headline: Centene (CNC) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of health coverage company Centene (NYSE:CNC) jumped 5.8% in the morning session after Baird raised its price target on the stock to $36 from $28, though the firm maintained its Neutral rating. The move from the investment firm suggested an improved outlook on the company's valuation, even as it stopped short of a full recommendation to buy the shares.
